On December 13, 2008, Tim Tebow finished third in the 2008 Heisman Trophy voting with Oklahoma's Sam Bradford taking the top spot followed by Texas' Colt McCoy, despite Tebow receiving the most first-place votes. Tim Tebow also won the Maxwell Award in 2008, becoming only the second player to win the award twice.

